orht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Ewenlode was born about 1165, in Coughton, Warwickshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Robert de Ewenlode, was 22 and his mother, Mrs. Robert de Ewenlode, was 18. He had at least 1 daughter with Eva Durvassall."},"et":{"Abt 1165–":"umbes 1165–Surnud","1165–Male":"1165–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1192–Female":"1192–Surnud","1144–Male":"1144–Surnud","1148–Female":"1148–Surnud","1148":"1148","1169":"1169","Abt 1165":"umbes 1165","1144":"1144","1165":"1165","1192":"1192","of Coughton, Warwick, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, England","Coughton, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Coughton, Alcester, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1165–":"noin 1165–Kuollut","1165–Male":"1165–Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1192–Female":"1192–Kuollut","1144–Male":"1144–Kuollut","1148–Female":"1148–Kuollut","1148":"1148","1169":"1169","Abt 1165":"noin 1165","1144":"1144","1165":"1165","1192":"1192","of Coughton, Warwick, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, England","Coughton, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Coughton, Alcester, Warwickshire, England":"Coughton, Warwickshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1165–":"environ 1165–Décédé","1165–Male":"1165–Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1192–Female":"1192–Décédée","1144–Male":"1144–Décédé","1148–Female":"